Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.48,0:00:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know where we were till I\Nrealized we were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.92,0:00:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\N>> Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.32,0:01:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello. Okay. Hi. Um, we have uh 10\Npeople that are from Korea that are in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.19,0:01:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the audience. If you could please stand\Nup. Stand up for us. They came all the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.40,0:01:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,way from from from Korea to be with us\Ntoday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.36,0:01:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Who Who are the 10 people? What?\N>> We have 10 people from Korea that are
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.84,0:01:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,here.\N>> Oh. Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.72,0:01:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> yeah.\NThere.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.56,0:01:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\Nyes. We appreciate you traveling such a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.20,0:01:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,long way. We also have a lot of people\Nhere from Canada. Where are the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.28,0:01:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Canadians? Okay, stand up. Let everybody\Ntake a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.60,0:01:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I I wanted to acknowledge them because\Nthey have come from such a long way and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.11,0:02:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a terrific following in Korea\Nand these people, you know, we really
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.79,0:02:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,appreciate it. They were one of the\Nfirst people that David and I uh did a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.11,0:02:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,seminar for uh was in Korea and we went\Nall the way over there. That was um I
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.76,0:02:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,think it was uh 99. In 99 we started it.\NNow Dr. Moon has a ashram there who is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.16,0:02:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,continuing with our teachings and she is\Ntranslating all the work into Korean for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.04,0:02:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,those people. So I just want to\Nacknowledge you and thank you so much
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.64,0:02:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for coming.\N>> Anybody here from Dubai today? Dubai.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.36,0:02:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here from Dubai?\Nask,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.23,0:02:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> do we have our Dubai people here today?\N>> Dubaiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.12,0:02:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I think she's coming to October, honey.\NUh, we have a couple of people that come
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.04,0:02:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,over from Dubai also. And um, they'll I\Nthink they said they were coming to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.92,0:02:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,October lecture\N>> or India. Or India.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.04,0:03:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> How about our Indian people? Is anyone\Nhere from India?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.48,0:03:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. Come on, stand up.\N>> Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.51,0:03:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Australia.\NAustralia. India.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.72,0:03:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Australia.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.08,0:03:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Stand up and let us see you.\N>> So, I just wanted to acknowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.04,0:03:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody.\NWe'd have everyone standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.79,0:03:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Um, there's going to be no recording\Nof the lecture. I don't know if any of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.72,0:03:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you are doing that, but we cannot have\Nyou record the lecture. Um, it's all
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.76,0:03:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,copyrighted. And so, if any of you are\Nrecording it, we'd ask you uh please
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.92,0:03:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,refrain from that. Thank you.\N>> Okay, we'll resume. We have exactly one
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.64,0:03:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,hour.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.48,0:04:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay, we got up to number 14. We better\Nmove along.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.72,0:04:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,value wisdom over being right. Uh it's\Nnot necessary to be right unless you're
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.59,0:04:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,uh you feel that you have to fight for\Nyour image. You know the image is that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.47,0:04:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to be right. Uh it's of greater\Nvalue to be understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.44,0:04:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,One one thing that people ignore in our\Ncurrent society,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.60,0:04:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but I learned in psychoanalysis and my\Nown training
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.00,0:04:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,was to seek wise counsel.\NYou don't have to solve everything all
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.28,0:04:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,by yourself without discussing it with\Nanybody. Everybody should have somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.24,0:04:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a mentor that they look up to, that they\Nrespect,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.80,0:04:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,uh can be just a very good friend.\NBut instead of keeping everything to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.91,0:04:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself and sweating it out, you can\Nyou can
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.96,0:05:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,talk to people that you respect because\Nyou get feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.00,0:05:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a reason for it other than just\Nthe practicality
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.80,0:05:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is you don't get so egotistic about\Nwhatever your conclusion is. I mean, you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.47,0:05:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't conclude to do that all by\Nyourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.08,0:05:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You discussed it with a friend and the\Ntwo of you decided that. Well, if the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.72,0:05:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,two of you decided that, then you don't\Nsay, "Well, I'm the one that won picked
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.03,0:05:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the winning ticket." You know what I\Nmean? I picked the winning ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.72,0:05:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you discuss the winning best ticket\Nto buy with somebody else, then it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.63,0:05:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,share joint decision\Nand that, you know, protects you from
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.68,0:05:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,egotistical\Nuh inflation. So, we're looking for ways
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.63,0:05:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend the ego and allow the\Nspirit to take over. And this is one of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.56,0:05:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the ways. In all my years in psychiatry\Nand psychoanalysis,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.44,0:06:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,uh it was another rule to always have a\Ncolleague to discuss things with. Even
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.56,0:06:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,though I'd had 50 years experience as a\Npsychiatrist, one time had for many
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.08,0:06:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,years the largest practice in the entire\NUnited States, I still had somebody that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.12,0:06:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw periodically\Nto discuss things with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.08,0:06:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get feedback from other people\Nand they have other ways of looking at
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.12,0:06:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it. And so sometimes my council would\Nsay, "Well, that sounds good, but you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.40,0:06:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,could look at it this way." Well, I\Nhadn't thought of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.00,0:06:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's good to have a confessor,\Nconfessor,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.91,0:06:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a counselor,\Na therapist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.75,0:06:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody should have a psychotherapist.\NEverybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.40,0:06:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anybody that doesn't need a\Npsychotherapist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.88,0:06:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The people who think they don't need a\Ntherapist
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.19,0:07:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,are the most gone of all.\NNo, I can do it on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.16,0:07:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, good luck.\NHave a good spouse. Have somebody that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.19,0:07:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you can confide in, share share in\Nreaching decisions and uh it it serves
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.59,0:07:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,your highest good to always have\Nsomebody to share with uh serves your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.52,0:07:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,highest good.\NThat's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.44,0:07:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I got you, babe. Yeah. Yeah. Yeah.\NOf course, it was wise counsel that led
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.56,0:08:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to me sharing things with you. Me,\Nuh, I'm so smart. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.40,0:08:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk to her with Susie and then make up\Nyour mind. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.24,0:08:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Realize that you influence others\Nby what you are, not just by what you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.87,0:08:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,do. We subtly are constantly influencing\Nactually all of mankind by what we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.08,0:08:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you are is more important than\Nwhat you do because what you are
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.36,0:08:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,radiates out an energy that influences\Neveryone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.59,0:08:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,what you are, what you have become is\Nmore powerful. People can say, "What can
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.95,0:08:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I do to help mankind?"\NAnd I tell them, "Become the, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.88,0:08:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the most loving evolved person that you\Ncan. Love all of life in all of its
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.48,0:08:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,expressions.\NBe respectful of nature and beauty. Uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.60,0:08:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,esteem, beauty, and nature.\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.32,0:09:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that you influence others by\Nwhat you are, not what you do. So this
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.39,0:09:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,group here right now is influencing\Nmankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.64,0:09:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This group is influencing mankind. We're\Nnot doing anything. We don't have any
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.16,0:09:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,flags to wave. We don't have any\Nslogans. We're not shouting into the TV
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.60,0:09:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,reporters microphone.\NThis group right here is influencing all
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.12,0:09:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind right now. Resist.\NThere you see. You radiate out an energy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.80,0:09:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,into the field of consciousness\Nwhich influences everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.60,0:09:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So that your best thing you can do for\Nthe world is to sit down and shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.08,0:09:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind thoughts that you have towards\Nothers, the kindly thoughts, the kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.20,0:10:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the intention that you have towards\Nothers
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.80,0:10:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to influence all of mankind. The\Nwhole field of consciousness of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.36,0:10:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that you are influencing others\Nright now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.44,0:10:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Not by what? Not by what you say, but\Nwhat you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.36,0:10:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why I am not an enthusiast of\Nactivism.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.44,0:10:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Activism,\Neverybody, you know, they get on TV and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.36,0:10:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they're and they have a thing around\Ntheir thing. They're a blogger activist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.80,0:10:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I salute all blogger activists.\NThat's my blogger activist salute. I
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.92,0:10:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,salute you.\NThey actually get on TV
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.64,0:10:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're being interviewed by the\Nchair of the thing and that's what
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.20,0:11:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,they're underneath it says blogger\Nactivist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.16,0:11:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked them what have they blogged\Nlately? Screw you. Oh yes. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.95,0:11:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\Navoid activism and pedantry. And people
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.27,0:11:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Well, isn't that the American\Nway?" It's the American way of certain
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.24,0:11:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,people in America at certain times, but\Nit's not a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.80,0:11:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you choose spirituality as a\Nlifestyle,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.88,0:11:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,as a lifestyle,\Nyou can give up the activist signs and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.12,0:11:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the parades, most of which is egoistic\Ndisplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.39,0:11:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Most activism is egocentricity.\NLook at me how important I am and listen
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.07,0:11:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to me because what I have to say is so\Nimportant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.00,0:11:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not important to anybody except you\Nbut anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.83,0:12:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds good on act. So you'll see on TV\Ninter you'll see it's interesting. It
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.72,0:12:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,says activist blogger and activist that\Nwas on this week. I said a blogger
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.68,0:12:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,activist. Boy, oh boy. There's only 150\Nmillion of them in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.04,0:12:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Be grateful for your assets.\NBe glad that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.63,0:12:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,um smart and good-looking\Nand that you're tolerant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.32,0:12:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And your biggest asset is that you have\Nbecome interested in spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.36,0:12:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and spirituality\Nand serving God and your fellow man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.20,0:12:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It is helpful to your ego to remind\Nyourself that mankind has survived
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.63,0:12:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,millions of years without your help.\NI don't know how mankind got along
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.95,0:13:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,without me all these years.\NSo intrinsic to spiritual evolution is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.12,0:13:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,humility.\NAnd therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.04,0:13:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,yours is the saddest story I've ever\Nheard is a good one. And you can also
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.63,0:13:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,add to it as a another sentence. Mankind\Nhas survived without you so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.12,0:13:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That way you don't take yourself so\Nseriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.63,0:13:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Take yourself so seriously\Nbe and by doing these things you become
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.95,0:13:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,your own best friend.\NPutting a little thing on your mirror
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.76,0:13:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that says yours is the saddest story I\Nhave ever heard
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.95,0:13:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and mankind has survived all millions of\Nyears without you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.95,0:13:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You're already being your best friend.\NYou're bringing your ego in. You're
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:14:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,putting a leash on your ego, reminding\Nyourself of the reality
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.80,0:14:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are of benefit to mankind.\NTo the degree that you radiate God's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.48,0:14:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,love, the degree that you radiate love,\Nunconditional love to the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.00,0:14:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you are your own best friend and you are\Ndoing everything you can to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.92,0:14:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is full of dogooders.\NAnd the history of dogooders is rather
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.44,0:14:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,cat catastrophic.\NThere's always a dogoodter and and they
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.24,0:14:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,like politics. They like to control\Nother people that for your own good
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.12,0:14:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to reduce the so and so and\Npeanut butter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.00,0:14:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They're after one thing another. Candy,\Npeanut butter, booze, smoking, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.32,0:14:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,chewing tobacco and whatever you want.\NThere's always a do goodter going to do
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.63,0:14:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,something. Do good for you. Do good for\Nyou. meaning control you. What they mean
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.48,0:15:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is they want to control you in a certain\Nway. It's for your own health.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.24,0:15:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not let me worry about my health?\NThe longer I live, the long the more it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.60,0:15:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,costs the taxpayer.\NI don't want people to quit smoking,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.27,0:15:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,quit drinking, and driving fast while\Nthey're blind drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.32,0:15:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an interesting book on dogooders\Nby Mono Sharen,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.56,0:15:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,real dogooders.\NI got to experience some of it in in
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.72,0:15:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,great great detail. At one time I had\Nthe largest psychiatric practice in the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.07,0:15:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,United States for many years and the\Ngreatest hospital practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.72,0:15:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh I was also in charge of many\Nhospitals, state hospitals where there
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.72,0:15:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,was 3,000, 5,000, even up to 9,000\Npatients all in a giant hospital. So the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.36,0:16:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,dogooders came along and said, "Well,\Nthere is no such thing as mental
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.68,0:16:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,illness. That's just a myth."\NI forget the idiot who said that, but I
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.24,0:16:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for he was. I invite him to have one of\Nthem live with him. We'll see how long
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.80,0:16:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,he thinks this\Nafter he burns down your house and stabs
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.12,0:16:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,your wife to death and rapes your\Ndaughter. We'll see how whether it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.12,0:16:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,myth or not. Anyway,\Ndo goodters was mental illness was a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.95,0:16:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,myth. I forgot the idiot some\Npsychiatrist who really uh he's probably
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.83,0:16:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,on the other side. I don't mean to say\Nanything mean about just about and it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.04,0:16:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,was stupid and uh\Nmental illness was just a myth. So they
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.80,0:16:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,opened the doors of the state hospitals\Nand let these poor victims out. You see
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.83,0:16:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,victimology\Npictured these poor souls as being the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.92,0:16:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,victims of the system and that the\Nhospital was like incarcerating.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.68,0:16:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the reality was that these people\Nwere not capable of taking care of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.51,0:17:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves on the outside. In fact,\Nthat's the main reason they're there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.60,0:17:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that they were mentally ill or\Nemotionally ill, but they frankly
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.28,0:17:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't take care of themselves. So,\Nthey closed the doors to the state
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.16,0:17:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,hospital and all these people went out\Ninto the street and they became today's
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.19,0:17:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,street people. The street people you see\Nin any big city
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.07,0:17:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,years back were in a middle hospital.\NWell, in the middle hospital, you got
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.28,0:17:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,three good meals a day balanced by\Ndieticians. You got free medical
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.40,0:17:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,treatment. You got legal protection,\Nmedical protection, you got all kinds of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.12,0:17:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,protection and things were done for you.\NYou never How often do those people go
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.20,0:17:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to the dentist laying on the street,\Ntheir teeth fall out in a mental
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.64,0:17:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,hospital? You see the dentist, etc.\NAnyway, Mona Sharin uh details that. Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.48,0:17:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,doters always have something wonderful.\NThey think it will be good for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.48,0:18:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Another thing that's wonderful is to let\Nother people win.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.96,0:18:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting others win is very gratifying\Nand uh it makes them very happy. So
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.96,0:18:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,letting other people win arguments, they\Nsay, "You're right, honey. You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.03,0:18:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, dear."\NShe does it with me. She said, "Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.36,0:18:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll do as you say." We'll do as you\Nsay. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.08,0:18:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we we do is I say because I\Nlet her win by saying we'll do what you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.40,0:18:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,say. That puts her on top. Now I got to\Nthink of a way to counter to be on top
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.52,0:18:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of that one.\NBeware of unintended consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.32,0:18:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very well known in society. You\Nintend to for a thing to go in a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.76,0:18:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,direction and there are other factors\Ninvolved that you're unaware of.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.79,0:19:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that in trying to develop\Ncompassion for people and their
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.32,0:19:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,propensity to make grave errors, the\Ngrave errors is the innocent child is
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.72,0:19:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,present in everyone.\NSo the innocent child in all of us reads
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.52,0:19:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the a book like dooodters and says let's\Ngo and save the mentally ill. They're
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.67,0:19:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,being imprisoned against their will and\Nmental illness is just a myth anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.96,0:19:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Who believes that the innocent child is\Npresent in everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.84,0:19:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You could also call it the idiot child.\NThe child is innocent, innocent and is
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.08,0:19:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,present in everyone.\NThe reason you believe what you believe
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.84,0:19:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is because the innocent child in you\Nbelieves it. Within us is the child, the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.28,0:20:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,adult and the parent is a good\Ndesignation. And so the child within you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.08,0:20:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,uh tends to believe the adult and\Nespecially the parent. So the parent
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.84,0:20:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,within you says, "Well, I read it in the\Npaper or I saw it on television or I
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.64,0:20:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,read a good book on it." Well, that's\Nenough to impress the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.44,0:20:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The innocent child is present in\Neveryone. Who makes the mistake when you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.40,0:20:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,screw up?\NWho is it that really screws up?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.12,0:20:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the innocent child.\NSo if you're going to blame somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.24,0:20:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you who are you going to blame? You\Ngoing to blame the parent, the super
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.55,0:20:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,ego? No. Going to you tend to blame the\Nadult, but it wasn't the adult that fell
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.40,0:20:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,for it. It was the innocent child. The\Ninnocent child then is what's gullible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.79,0:20:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the political discussions that\Nyou hear so heatedly on Fox News and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.12,0:21:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,others uh is appealing to the innocent\Nchild and other people. This one must
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.40,0:21:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,know what they're talking about. Oh,\Nokay. Cuz they got this title. I'm the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.15,0:21:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,zar of something. They must know what\Nthey're talking about. The innocent
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.67,0:21:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,child believes that.\NUh the government believes it. The
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.28,0:21:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,voters believe it.\NUh,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.28,0:21:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,who would even suspect the innocent\Nchild doesn't know his ass from a hot
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.03,0:21:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,rock?\NHow can a zar not know his what? From a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.40,0:21:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,hot rock.\NHe didn't even pay his own income taxes
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.12,0:21:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,yet.\NAll right. Pray to see things
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.48,0:21:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,differently. It brings up the whole\Nreframe and recontextualize.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.76,0:21:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What does a thing mean?\NMeans
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.03,0:22:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what does it mean? It means if you frame\Nit this way, this is the way it looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.60,0:22:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you frame it differently, it\Nlooks different. It's the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.64,0:22:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing you've changed is the\Nframe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.24,0:22:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If I take an idiot and he babbles\Nidiocy, I say he's a dumb nut.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.48,0:22:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If I give him a title, congressman from\Nsomeplace, brother, I've recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.88,0:22:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,him. Now he's a politician. A minute ago\Nhe was a dumb nut, but now I've reframed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.40,0:22:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,him.\NCritics are a dime a dozen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.84,0:22:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that the majority of people\Ncalibrate below 200. All right? So you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.48,0:22:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,won't be disappointed. Your peace will\Nnot be disturbed because your
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.55,0:22:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,expectation of people is if they survive\Nand are pleasant, that in itself is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.76,0:22:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,fantastic.\NThe fact that they're surviving and they
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.08,0:23:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,still got a job or they're still taking\Ncare of the kids, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.96,0:23:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh the majority of people calibrate\Nbelow 200. Now we showed that with the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.00,0:23:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,graph before. So mankind is not anywhere\Nnear as evolved as you think it is. A
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.79,0:23:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of the criticism that we have of\Nothers, politics or anything else in our
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.60,0:23:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,society is the expectation of a higher\Nlevel of consciousness than the people
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.88,0:23:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,are capable of. The majority of people\Ncannot tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.84,0:23:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a shock?\NBoy, oh boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.20,0:23:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,H\NI have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.20,0:23:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a fact. Resist.\NDoes that reframe your understanding of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.91,0:23:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the human condition?\NThe he
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.88,0:24:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the human mind,\Nhumanity, people, whole nations, whole
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.12,0:24:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,civilizations\Nare unable to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.32,0:24:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Whole societies, whole civilizations,\Nwhole generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.20,0:24:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a whole generation of Germans\Nprior to World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.24,0:24:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,mine comp\Nmillions of people worshiping this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.88,0:24:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He's going to be the savior of write the\Nwrongs of World War I and all this lead
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.79,0:24:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind to new uh pure a pure race and\Nall.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.12,0:24:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, "How can millions of people\Nfollow a guy who calibrates about 170?"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.60,0:24:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see in other countries right\Nnow, dictators around the world all
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.36,0:24:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate about 170.\NYou want a brain surgeon who calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.00,0:24:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,at 170?\NI don't even want a cook that calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.60,0:25:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at 170.\NSo, we tailor our expectations of the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.76,0:25:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,world. We become more forgiving because\Nwe realize that error is due to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.72,0:25:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,ignorance and it's due to the child, the\Ninner child within oneself. If you can
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.64,0:25:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,impress anyone's inner child, that's\Nwhat convinces people. And that's what
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.27,0:25:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the media do constantly. They try to\Nimpress the inner child.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.24,0:25:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll give somebody a fantastic title,\NZar. Zar,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.15,0:25:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the Zar of something. Oh boy, the Zar\Nmust know something about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.67,0:25:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This doesn't know anything\Nexcept the majority of people calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.20,0:25:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200.\NAll right. Now those who are spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.32,0:25:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,oriented\Nuh judge not lest you be judged. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.84,0:26:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So that does not mean to go to sleep and\Nbe unaware of reality and the essence of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.52,0:26:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,things. But what does it mean?\NWhat it means is they realize that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.08,0:26:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,people cannot help themselves because of\Ntheir own inner limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.36,0:26:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There therefore everyone is\Nintrinsically innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.76,0:26:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If they could be better than they are,\Nthey would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.44,0:26:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,To say they could be better is a\Nhypothetical egotism.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.00,0:26:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In reality, you cannot be better than\Nyou are.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.48,0:26:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Judge not, lest ye be judged. Uhhuh.\NTherefore, who's the motives in whose
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.60,0:26:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,eye? Judge not.\NIt doesn't mean to be
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.88,0:26:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,blind to the reality of what people are.\NTo recognize that somebody is a crook
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.64,0:27:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,who's on the take\Nuh is merely a recognition of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.67,0:27:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's different than judgmentalism.\NJudgmentalism says he shouldn't be that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.96,0:27:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,way. Well, if he could if he could be\Ndifferent than he is, he would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.32,0:27:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All viewpoints are arbitrary. All\Nviewpoints are arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.67,0:27:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because they all represent\Noppositionality
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.67,0:27:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and a and the result of framing. Look at\Nfrom this viewpoint, it looks like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.52,0:27:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Look that from this point viewpoint, it\Nlooks like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.76,0:27:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So all viewpoints are arbitrary\Nand therefore you judge not.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.08,0:27:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nrealize that any judgment you can make
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.36,0:27:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,represents a viewpoint and that\Nviewpoint itself is arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.44,0:27:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So that saves us the problem of getting\Ninto fixed fixed positionalities of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.84,0:28:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,rigidity.\NA spiritually evolved person avoids
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.88,0:28:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,rigidity doesn't mean they have they\Nlose certainty about the reality as they
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.39,0:28:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,have known it. But it's no longer an\Narbitrary position.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.88,0:28:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There are lots of people don't believe\Nin God and I understand them completely
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.44,0:28:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and they get on and they rant and rave\Nabout the evil of religion and godness
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.27,0:28:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that. And I myself was a devout\Nuh atheist for 20 years or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.60,0:28:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't no I wasn't an atheist. I was a\Nnon-believer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.20,0:28:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I was extremely religious very\Nreligious.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.27,0:28:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then due to a very major inner\Npsychic event,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.91,0:28:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I switched from being\Nuh very religious to the point of hyper
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.55,0:28:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,religiosity\Nand instantly became an agnostic,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.55,0:29:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,became an atheist actually and later on\Nan agnostic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.39,0:29:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh I think I've told that before. I was\Nwalking through the woods one day. You
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.67,0:29:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,know, I had a very religious upbringing.\NI was a boat boy for the bishop. I was
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.48,0:29:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,an acolyte. I sang in the church choir.\NI was a boy soloist at the cathedral. I
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.03,0:29:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,was about as religious as you could get.\NAnd our family was religious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.08,0:29:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And one day I was walking through the\Nwoods,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.91,0:29:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,not thinking about religion or God or\Nanything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.67,0:29:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, out of nowhere arose\Na vision of the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.84,0:29:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering of all of mankind\Nthroughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.52,0:29:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a revelation. Suddenly the\Ncurtain was pulled aside and I saw
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.91,0:30:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the enormity and gravity of the\Nsuffering of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.27,0:30:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that instant I became an atheist.\NI said I can't believe in a god who
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.72,0:30:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,allow that.\NSo I blame the suffering of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.79,0:30:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,on god.\NWhat I didn't realize that would have
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.64,0:30:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,been revealed to me was not divinity but\Nthe ego. What I was looking at is the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.52,0:30:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,profound destruction and massive agony\Nand suffering that the ego has brought
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.44,0:30:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,man over time.\NThat which is demonic, the devil, you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.55,0:30:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever you want to call it, that which\Nis evil, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.08,0:30:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it took me a good 20 years to\Ndiscover the mistake I had made. It
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.32,0:30:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't God responsible for all that, but\Nmankind himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.60,0:31:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Ngreediness is not taught by God. It's so
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.44,0:31:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the suffering of mankind is then brought\Nabout by the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.24,0:31:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't even blame the ego because it's\Nthe innocence of the inner child that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.24,0:31:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,believes the ego.\NSo man's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.79,0:31:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering then really arises\Nout of his lack of spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.72,0:31:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ignorance that accompanies uh\Nbeing deaf, dumb and blind to the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.60,0:31:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of divinity.\NAnd therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.00,0:31:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,God uh was reborn.\NGod was happy about it. Geez Dave, thank
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.96,0:31:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,God you made that.\NYeah. Yes. Except that the majority of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.51,0:31:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,people calvaryate below 200. There's the\Nsource of man's suffering. All
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.12,0:31:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,viewpoints are arbitrary.\NTherefore, we renew thankfulness and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.84,0:32:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,gratitude.\NEvery day we say, "Our father who art in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.36,0:32:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,heaven," etc.\NI watch the ice road truckers, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.08,0:32:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,they're back on again. And this guy is,\Nis he driving this truck? He's saying
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.84,0:32:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the Lord's Prayer out loud. 30 below\Nzero in this huge giant truck and he's
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.03,0:32:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,about, you know, a half a minute from\Ndeath on this icebreak series. He's a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.76,0:32:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,dead goner, you know, and he's saying\Nthe Lord's Prayer out loud. Our father
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.00,0:32:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in heaven, he says as he drives this\Ntruck up near Alaska.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.67,0:32:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Very uh impressive. I don't know. He he\Nhe's very impressive his
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.27,0:32:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,simplicity.\NAll right. So we renew our thankfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.51,0:32:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and gratitude.\NAnd now a really re really liberating
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.64,0:32:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding.\NThe mind which you consider yourself is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.88,0:33:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,not you. It's an it.\NThe mind is what talks all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.72,0:33:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What talks is not the spirit but the\Nego. The spirit doesn't talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.60,0:33:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind isn't it. It's not who you are.\NIn the enlightened state, you realize
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.76,0:33:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not the body.\NYou're not the mind. You are something
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.64,0:33:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that goes beyond and encompasses both of\Nthem. The mind is an it. It's not a you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.76,0:33:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you listen to the mind, you can\Nrefer to it as it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.39,0:33:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it thinking about taking this\Ndriveway home? Huh? That's what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.15,0:33:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking.\NNot you. The real eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.91,0:33:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The real eye, the self with a capital S\Nis the presence of divinity within. The
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.72,0:33:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,radiance of consciousness itself without\Nwhich you wouldn't even know that you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.72,0:33:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,exist.\NThe source of all awareness is the self
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.84,0:34:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with a capital S which is not different\Nthan c consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.32,0:34:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness then is the radiance of\Ndivinity as all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.00,0:34:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The radiance of all that exists. Out of\Nconsciousness arises the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.20,0:34:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of consciousness arises the universe\Nand all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.87,0:34:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is an it is not a you. And\Ncritics are a dime a dozen. People say,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.00,0:34:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, that's the American way to get up\Nand uh speak your peace." I think that's
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.15,0:34:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful that people do that. And then\Nthey should sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.32,0:34:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold your sign up here. I have here what\Nyou have to say. And then I say, "Thank
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.52,0:34:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you.\NNext."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.07,0:35:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOkay. Now accepting that the people
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.76,0:35:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,majority of people below 200 is a little\Nmore difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.32,0:35:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to help you with this review\Nextraordinary popular delusions and the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.80,0:35:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,madness of crowds. I refer to this book\Nvery often because all of mankind or the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.40,0:35:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,majority of mankind can be seriously\Nwrong about basic facts of life and the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.72,0:35:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,fact that it's held generally by the\Npopulace uh makes it true. Right now we
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.96,0:35:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,have earth warming uh challenging as\Nnumber one belief system and we'll get
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.04,0:35:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to that later. Review extraordinary\Npopular delusions in the madness of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.76,0:35:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,crowds. So the fact that everybody\Nbelieves the thing is interesting should
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.80,0:35:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,be taken into account but it should not\Nbe persuasive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.11,0:36:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep a sense of humor.\NOh,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.16,0:36:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you know they're going to tax people.\NThe go f the government going to tax
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.68,0:36:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,people for cattle.\NEvery cow is going to cost you a $15
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.80,0:36:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,federal tax. The reason is is because\Ncattle emit methane.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.68,0:36:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Methane is a cause of earth warming.\NCattle, you know what's are what's
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.64,0:36:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,causing the earth to warm.\NJust think what went on when there were
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.24,0:36:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,70 million bison running across the face\Nof the United States. 70 million bison
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.00,0:36:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,all doing you know what\Nmust have made quite a noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.80,0:36:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The earth would have gone into a fiery\Nball.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.83,0:37:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,70 million bison emitting b methane at\Nthe same to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.68,0:37:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so earthwarming is today's uh major\Ndelusion and madness of the crowd. And
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.52,0:37:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it's so politicized, you know, it's so\Npoliticized.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.35,0:37:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody gets out there about\Nearthworming. It becomes very fervent,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.83,0:37:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,very fervent.\NCertain politicians whose names I won't
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.48,0:37:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,mention, they aren't going to allow\Nsomething or other because that's going
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.83,0:37:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to save the earth. Oh, you're going to\Nsave the earth. Yeah. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.28,0:37:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone assumes that they are right and\Nothers are wrong. So when you hear an
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.48,0:37:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,argument going on, put yourself in the\Nother person's place and say to their
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.72,0:37:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,hearing what I'm saying is wrong.\NSo when I discuss maybe an alternate
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.16,0:37:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,view of what's causing earthwarming,\NI'm aware that the other person has been
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.72,0:38:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,thoroughly brainwashed and is not\Nbelieving as what I say at all. I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.92,0:38:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,even know why I'm talking to him except\Nthat you have to be polite and make
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.07,0:38:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation. So I say, well, an\Nalternate view is that earthwarming has
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.83,0:38:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to do with the magnetic activity on the\Nsurf of the sun and sunspots as ice core
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.48,0:38:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,drillings back through 10 million years\Nhave demonstrated. Uh that's just an
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.72,0:38:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,alternate view. So um I don't care if\Nthey believe it or not. I mean it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.32,0:38:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't hurt me if they want to tax\Ncows.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.07,0:38:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh seek to understand other than change\Nthem. So it's not necessary to change
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.11,0:38:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,people to see things your way. Serve God\Nrather than the narcissistic ego. To
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.68,0:38:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,serve God means to spiritually\Nsend forth love and good will towards
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.11,0:38:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,people. Send forth good will.\Ngood will towards all of life in all its
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.28,0:39:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,expressions. So the rule of life that I\Nthink I recommend
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.59,0:39:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is to serve all of life and have\Nreverence for all of life and all its
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.72,0:39:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,expressions.\NAnd therefore all you have to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.68,0:39:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,participate rather than dominate. You\Ndon't have to win every argument. You
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.32,0:39:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,can put a thought in the other person's\Nmind and say so I have heard. Wasn't it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.32,0:39:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the Buddha that said that all the time?\NAs I have heard. As I have heard. So
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.28,0:39:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I I like to say uh I have heard. And\Nthen you can give them an alternate
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.76,0:39:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,view.\NUh and it's okay to have faults.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.07,0:39:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I have faults. When Yogi Bear that said,\N"I have faults, but being wrong ain't
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.76,0:39:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,one of them."\NI got false, but being wrong ain't one
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.59,0:40:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of them. It's described to Yogi Bara. I\Ndon't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.80,0:40:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, now we we reach the peak of our\Ncurrent society in the that's the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.07,0:40:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,struggle for the moral high ground.\NWho's right? Who's morally therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.20,0:40:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,superior?\NSupport others to find good about
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.52,0:40:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves\Neven though they're a psychotic raving
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.83,0:40:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,idiot.\NThey're kind to their mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.76,0:40:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You are very kind to your mother. Yeah.\NFind something good and you can really
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.35,0:40:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,cook. You can really cook, you know, fry\Nbacon really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.88,0:40:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Concede therefore to what is versus what\Nyou think things ought to be. All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.88,0:40:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So you got to watch out when your mind\Nstart telling you things ought to be
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.76,0:40:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,such and such a way. Be very suspicious\Nof ought the things that ought to be
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.07,0:41:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,different. People ought to be smarter.\NNo. Why? People ought to agree with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.35,0:41:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No. People ought to pay their taxes\Nhonestly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.56,0:41:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean ought?\Nuntil you get the bizarre
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.31,0:41:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,concentr\Nthat we people will take advantage of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.35,0:41:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,loopholes\Nif they're left open instead of making
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.31,0:41:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,them wrong about that. You can blame it\Non human nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.59,0:41:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's human nature to chisel a little bit\Nif you can get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.92,0:41:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's human nature to chisel if they can\Nget away with it. And the majority of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.28,0:41:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,people calibrate under 200.\NTherefore, the majority of people
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.07,0:41:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,would cheat on their income tax if they\Ncould get away with it. Let's see. We
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.04,0:42:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,have permission to ask that. It's true.\NWhat do you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.96,0:42:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh,\NI call it creative tax reporting.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.88,0:42:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Naming your cat as a dependent.\NDeducting your veterinarian bills as
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.76,0:42:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,medical treatment.\NMy doggy shots. deducted as medical
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.31,0:42:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,treatment. Yeah.\NConcede to what is. So there's no point
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.59,0:42:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in pe making people wrong about that.\NEverybody's into survival and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.31,0:42:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,they do what they think will will bring\Nabout increase the likelihood and value
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.04,0:43:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of their survival.\NSo we can just presume that people will
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.40,0:43:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,do what they consider uh best for their\Nsurvival.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.11,0:43:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. It's okay to just be rather than\Nto do or have
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.20,0:43:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the the all levels of consciousness were\Nwhat you have or what you do is what
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.92,0:43:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,makes you important.\NYour title, what you do, what you do,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.59,0:43:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what you have, cars, Cadillacs, private\Nplanes, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.88,0:43:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And in in the end it's what you have\Nbecome. It's what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.16,0:43:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender your will to God and therefore\Nyou can let bygones be bygones.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.83,0:43:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandmother used to say on the\Nmaternal side she'd say she was saintly.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.83,0:43:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact she was considered for\Nsaintthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.59,0:44:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't have anything good to say\Nabout a person, then don't say nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.92,0:44:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,anything at all.\NWell, you'll see the mind really likes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.76,0:44:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to uh say things that are not too\Ncomplimentary about people. That's what
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.72,0:44:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,gossip is all about.\NAnd when I was young, the in the church,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.48,0:44:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the women's organizations in the church,\Ntheir main problem, their main character
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.40,0:44:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,defect that they all worked on was the\Nattractiveness of gossip.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.00,0:44:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And I worked in a I worked in a uh\Nsomething about gardening. I forget the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.83,0:44:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,name of it. Greenhouse one time. And\Nthere was five or six women and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.64,0:44:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. And all they did all day was\Ngossip. That's all they did. They didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.96,0:44:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,have TV.\NSo, look at gossip obviously as a source
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.80,0:44:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of amusement. I'm sure if they had\Ntelevision, they would have turned it
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.52,0:45:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,on. But the conversation went, "Did you\Nsee the way Gertude look at him?" And
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.64,0:45:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,did you see what she was wearing? She\Nwore the same thing last time. Just so,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.40,0:45:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, that's the way the whole thing\Nwent. And I listened to that for eight
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.92,0:45:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,hours as I stuck these seedlings in. So\NI got an enormous education in gossip.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.48,0:45:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't have anything good to say\Nabout a person, then say nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.59,0:45:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Otherwise, the first negative\Nthing you can people see people run. Did
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.31,0:45:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you hear that so and so got a ticket for\Nso and so? Uhhuh. He got a ticket for
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.04,0:45:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,driving drunk. I hear. Yeah. No wonder\Nhis wife is.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.31,0:45:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to realize that mankind\Nhas been at war 93% of recorded history.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.68,0:46:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,93% of time man has been at war. Right\Nnow I don't remember how many wars we
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.20,0:46:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,got going on in the world. United States\Nhas two of them. But since I've been in
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.44,0:46:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the world, when I first was born, World\NWar I wasn't quite was just over and the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.64,0:46:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,shell shocked war veterans were uh\Nwanding around looking for jobs, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.40,0:46:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then since I've been around, uh I've\Nbeen I've lived through I don't know six
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.07,0:46:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,or seven wars. It's been one war after\Nanother.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.83,0:46:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If you count little wars in Africa and\Nvarious places, I guess it's been
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.04,0:46:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,there's been a war all the time I've\Nbeen alive this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.35,0:46:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So for 82 years at at least I know man\Nhas been at war.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.68,0:46:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All usually several wars at the same\Ntime.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.00,0:46:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do you think of that?\NSo there you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.80,0:47:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So there you are.\NMankind has been at war almost all the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.24,0:47:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,time. The only time he wasn't at war, he\Nwas probably sick with the plague and
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.80,0:47:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,too sick to be at war or too\Nimpoverished he couldn't even afford to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.28,0:47:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,buy a Tommy Hawk.\NI share this with Brock once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.52,0:47:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,saying, "So there you are.\NThe news in the morning is that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.20,0:47:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,something other happened, you know, and\NI say, well, so there you are."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.48,0:47:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In a way that's being fatalistic.\NSo there you are means that's the way
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.83,0:47:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the world runs. That's the way things\Nare in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.56,0:47:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that infuriates do gooders who feel that\Nthey shouldn't be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.72,0:48:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't be that way.\NI accept the fact that there will be
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.24,0:48:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,lots of people in the world who say it\Nshouldn't be that way, but it is that
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.07,0:48:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,way.\NSo there you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.92,0:48:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Another way to explain it is what will\Nbe will be. And what will be will be is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.56,0:48:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,not just chance. What will be will be is\Nvery hard to describe verbally. It has
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.59,0:48:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to do with the influence of karmic\Ninfluences.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.52,0:48:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, karmic influence, it's like we're\Nall little magnetic
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.20,0:48:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,uh we're all little like pieces of iron\Nfilings with a magnetic head north pole
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.55,0:48:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and south pole and the infinite field of\Nconsciousness which is the mind of God
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.11,0:48:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is an infinite magnetic field.\NNow, what you have become
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.55,0:49:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,determines where you are within that\Nfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.55,0:49:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've got a picture yourself as an\Niron filing. You've got a north pole and
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.04,0:49:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a south pole.\NHere's this big powerful electromagnetic
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.96,0:49:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,field, the mind of God called\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.88,0:49:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now where you are within the field\Ndepends on the decisions that you make.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.92,0:49:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you say, well, I'll forgive that\Nperson, you move up here higher in the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.64,0:49:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,field. And if you say, "I'm going to get\Neven with that son of a bitch," you move
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.11,0:49:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,down on the field.\NSo, you can't blame it on God. See, what
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.92,0:49:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,historical religions do is blame it on\NGod. This creates a lot of atheists in
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.16,0:49:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the world.\NNo,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.59,0:49:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,what what happens to you is solely up to\Nyou alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.59,0:49:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgive him.\NI hate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.55,0:49:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look. Overlook it. Now get even. You\Ncan see how a little electromagnetic
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.04,0:50:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,iron filing how you move in the infinite\Nmagnetic field. The infinite power of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.80,0:50:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself.\NThe power of consciousness is beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.04,0:50:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,man's imagination.\NWe've quoted the scientific explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.07,0:50:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy the p the power one cubic cm\Nof consciousness is greater than its
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.76,0:50:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,equivalent as weight of the entire\Nuniverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.00,0:50:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,One cubic inch of the infinite field of\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.96,0:50:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is equivalent is greater than the total\Nmass of the entire universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.55,0:50:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire mass of the universe is less\Nthan the power
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.76,0:50:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of a tiny bit of consciousness. Why?\NBecause the consciousness is the field
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.11,0:51:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of God's will. And the power of God's\Nwill is infinite. Has no beginning, has
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.24,0:51:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,no end, and is infinite\Nacceptance. So there you are. That's how
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.68,0:51:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it is.\NOh, okay. Develop a peaceful nature. Be
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.24,0:51:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,aware of the power of nature. Love\Nnature and develop yourself a a peaceful
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.04,0:51:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,nature.\NSee the beauty of all that exists. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.20,0:51:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Value quietude. Value quietude. You\Ndon't have to turn the radio on the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.44,0:51:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,instant you walk into the house.\NThe enemy of is really the inner child,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.96,0:51:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the innocence of the inner child and the\Ninner child's willfulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.48,0:51:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As spiritual beings, we practice the\Nvirtues. We don't claim perfection. We
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.07,0:51:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,claim progress. We try our best to\Nforgive people even though they seem to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.04,0:52:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,be uh evil or wrong or whatever. We\Npractice the virtues. doesn't say we
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.00,0:52:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,master the virtues. It says we practice\Nthem. So we're admitting that we are
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.83,0:52:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,evolutionary\Nthat the degree of our fulfillment of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.31,0:52:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our human potential is in constant\Nconstantly growing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.00,0:52:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Recall when you this is a very good one\Nbecause very often the power of this
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.04,0:52:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,arises in childhood. Recall peace on\Nearth, goodwill towards men, the angels
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.76,0:52:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,who announce the coming of Christ on\NChristmas Eve. Strive to be angelic
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.64,0:52:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than luciferic. Okay. Practice no\Nattractions and no aversions. The Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.72,0:52:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,said neither attractions nor aversions.\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.35,0:52:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to quit.\NPeople
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.20,0:53:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,are afraid of death.\NActually, the near-death experience is
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.92,0:53:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,one of absolute and total peace. So, the\Ngoal, the lecture for today has to do
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.00,0:53:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with peace and peacefulness.\NAnd although people fear death, the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.64,0:53:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,actual experience is one of infinite\Npeace.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.40,0:53:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we'll stop there for now.\NGod bless you. God bless you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.24,0:53:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We purposely came back a little late so\Nyou wouldn't feel guilty about getting
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.92,0:54:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,back late.\NWe want everybody to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.83,0:54:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,102 ways of happiness.\NOh dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.92,0:54:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,H\Nno attractions, no aversions. That
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.72,0:54:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,requires some discipline.\NUh you can do it by asking yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.40,0:54:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,could I let go wanting to be attracted\Nby that?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.07,0:54:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And you begin to see that the attraction\Nis something you project on to things.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.44,0:54:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That famous book that I've mentioned a\Nnumber of times called glamour
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.35,0:54:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,says a thing is not attractive at all.\NIts attraction is due to an energy that
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.16,0:54:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you project onto it.\NNow that's quite a surprise, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.24,0:54:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You think the attraction is in the\Nthing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.59,0:55:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction is in you. Yeah.\NYou're very attracted to a donut.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.11,0:55:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're hungry and you like donuts,\Nif you don't like donuts, if you hate
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.11,0:55:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,them, you don't think donuts are\Nattractive. You think they're ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.59,0:55:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugly donuts.\NHow to be how to be one up in a
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.76,0:55:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,conversations. You're going to have an\Nargument. I I'll tell you an inner
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.16,0:55:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,secret. You're going to have an argument\Nwith somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.20,0:55:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,their debater. So the person gets the\Nbear gets up with you and you say you
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.64,0:56:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,got something on your chin.\NIs that mayonnaise?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.52,0:56:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, try it sometime\Nin in a in a inaccurious
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.88,0:56:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in a harmless situation. Just say, "Is\Nis that something on your chin?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.76,0:56:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that ketchup?" No. Is that lettuce?\NIs that mayonnaise on your chin?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.59,0:56:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,\Nso that completely throws the other
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.76,0:56:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,person off their mindset.\NThrows them off their mindset and then
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.20,0:56:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you swoop in\Nwaiting for them like a hawk on the edge
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.72,0:57:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of the field. Is that mayonnaise on your\Nchin?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.83,0:57:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They've lost the g.\NYou throw them off. You throw them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.79,0:57:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They're cool.\NYeah, that I learned that in boxing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.64,0:57:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How to pretend. It's called the faint.\NAnd of course, I was a for formidable
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.92,0:57:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,mosquito weight.\NThey didn't have mosquito weight. They
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.88,0:57:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,invented mosquito weight for me.\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.16,0:57:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,except the social roles of others. In\Nother words, people are fulfilling what
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.40,0:57:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,they see as their social role. It's not\Nreally actually who they are. They're
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.04,0:57:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,acting out a social role and their\Ndefinition of the understanding of how
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.40,0:57:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,they're supposed to be and what they're\Nsupposed to be and how they're supposed
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.59,0:57:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to look and how they're supposed to\Ntalk. So everybody has a whole set of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.92,0:58:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,programs of what uh their behavior and\Nappearance and everything should be
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.11,0:58:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,like. So that's the value of trying to\Nunderstand others. To understand what
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.31,0:58:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,runs them and out of that comes\Ncompassion. Out of that arises
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.68,0:58:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,compassion. Understanding others brings\Ncompassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.24,0:58:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The near-death experience is one of\Ntotal peace. Uh, which is hard to
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.24,0:58:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,explain. But the peace, the peace of God\Nthat goes beyond understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.48,0:58:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is a peace of great profoundity,\Ntransforms the appearance of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.00,0:58:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and takes you out of all possible\Nsuffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.92,0:58:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next. We've got 101 of these. we\Nbetter move along.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.68,0:58:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the ego is vulnerable. The real\Nself is eternal. The real self is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.79,0:59:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,invisible to other people. And\Ntherefore, if your feelings are hurt or
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.00,0:59:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you feel you got to have something or\Nwin something or you're lamenting losing
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.55,0:59:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,something, remind yourself it's only the\Nex the ego creating this experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.68,0:59:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only the ego creating this\Nexperience. It's because of your
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.16,0:59:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship to the object that you\Nmourn it when it's lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.72,0:59:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So again, it's always going back to the\Nego to understand the ego and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.31,0:59:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,not be its victim, be its master instead\Nof its victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.44,0:59:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Live in each instant which is innately\Npeaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.35,0:59:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This comes about through spiritual work\Nalso
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.52,0:59:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to live not one day at a time, not one\Nhour at a time, one instant at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.11,0:59:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We were either going to make it back\Nhere in time or we weren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.48,1:00:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What can I do?\NI'm not driving. The traffic is there
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.72,1:00:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and helping or not helping. You say you\Nlive in each instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.79,1:00:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you live in each instant, you are\Nalways in peace because suffering is
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.40,1:00:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,created by writing a a a scenario,\Nwriting a story.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.20,1:00:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost poor so- and so and he got run\Nover by a so and so and then my cat got
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.96,1:00:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,drowned and then the next thing you know\NI had a flat tire and then I got a
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.55,1:00:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,ticket. I mean, you got a whole you got\Na whole long story. You see,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.16,1:00:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,uh,\Nnow actually the cop giving you a
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.52,1:00:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,ticket, you could say anytime I got a\Nticket, I always thanked him and I said,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.04,1:00:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"Thank you for helping to save my life."\NWell, he then he'd say, "Well, I was
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.40,1:00:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,going to write you a ticket."\NI said, "I realize you're actually
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.76,1:01:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,having to save my life and I'm so\Nstupid. I don't realize it." And the cop
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.40,1:01:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,would say, "Well, thank you, but watch\Nit from now on."
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.83,1:01:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Detach from control. Be the witness\Nobserver. This is a little more
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.88,1:01:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,sophisticated.\NIt means that if you constantly let go
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.64,1:01:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting to control things, change them,\Nbeing on top of them, what happens is
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.59,1:01:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the chatter of the ego stops and you\Nthen become merely the observer, the
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.07,1:01:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,witness. Now this is a high spiritual\Nstate in which you relinquish the
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.79,1:01:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,personal self to the field of\Nconsciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.68,1:01:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Witnessing and observing, you think\Nthere's a you doing that. There is no
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.55,1:01:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you witnessing or observing.\NThere isn't any person there at all. The
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.72,1:01:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,idea there's a person there comes in\Nafter you've observed and witnessed.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.68,1:02:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Observing and witnessing goes on\Nautonomously of its own. It doesn't need
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.04,1:02:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a personal self. Doesn't need a personal\Nself. Consciousness is aware.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.40,1:02:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't have to interject yourself\Nand say I'm aware. You said the edge of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.96,1:02:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the stage is there. The edge of the\Nstage is there. I don't know where the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.64,1:02:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,hell is the edge of the stage. Come.\NIt's there someplace. The edge of the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.07,1:02:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,stair is there.\NThe witness observer then is um a higher
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.55,1:02:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,state because the ego is not making\Nconclusions, judgments, doesn't want to
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.00,1:02:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,control anything. It merely wants to\Nwitness
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.72,1:02:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and when you go out of body uh at least\Nwhen I went out of body there was only
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.11,1:02:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the witness observer there didn't have\Nany particular
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.76,1:03:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,uh intention about anything it was just\Naware of it like people who leave the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.16,1:03:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,body and in surgery and go up to the\Nceiling and and witness the surgery
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.64,1:03:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the witness observer\Ndoesn't want to do anything but watches
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.28,1:03:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,everything. Just watches. Say, "What did\Nyou do when you're up near the ceiling?"
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.83,1:03:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't do anything, but I was aware of\Nwhat was going on. Be the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.76,1:03:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,observer. That's a state you can achieve\Nby constant surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.83,1:03:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and by uh contemplation.\NThe contemplative state puts you in the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.31,1:03:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,witness observer.\Nputs you in the witness observer.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.68,1:03:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Practice meditation and contemplation.\NAs you do that, the witness observer
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.64,1:03:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,uh becomes uh predominant\Nand becomes more or less one's normal
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.48,1:03:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,state.\NAnd uh
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.24,1:03:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the only trouble with that is you're\Nasking people questions all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.35,1:04:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What day is it?\NDifferentiate wants from needs.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.79,1:04:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What you want is one thing and what you\Nneed is another. People convince
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.28,1:04:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves that their wants are their\Nneeds. Uh they always have to have a
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.35,1:04:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,raise. Everybody Everybody has to have\Nmore money. That's universal.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.48,1:04:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how much you make, you need\Nmore money. If you ask any
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.88,1:04:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,multi-billionaire,\N"What's your problem?" He says, "Well, I
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.24,1:04:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I just need more\Ncapital.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.24,1:04:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I could buy the whole United States\Ninstead of just the eastern seabboard,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.92,1:04:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.\NAnd Jesus Christ said, "Wear the world
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.00,1:04:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,like a light garment." In other words,\Nparticipate. See that it's there.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.24,1:04:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh but it's not this not central. The\Nego is not central. Wear the world like
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.88,1:04:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,a light garment. So you're the witness\Nobserver. You observe the world and
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.11,1:05:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,differentiate appearance from essence.\NAnd that's what what we do when we use
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.40,1:05:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the arm to calibrate something.\NThe appearance of a thing is one thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.11,1:05:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence is another.\NThe ego cannot tell essence from
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.59,1:05:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance.\NIt just sees the wolf and sheep's
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.96,1:05:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,clothing. And uh the w the sheep and\Nwolf's clothing rather the wolf and
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.68,1:05:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,sheep's clothing differentiate\Nappearance from essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.52,1:05:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Be kind to all of life. Why? For its own\Nsake.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.64,1:05:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of your own reverence for life.\NBecause of your own reverence for life.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.64,1:05:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to be kind to all of life in all\Nof its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.52,1:05:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh no matter whether it's a toad or a\Nbunny or a squirrel, uh whether it's
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.48,1:05:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,another human being, whether it's a\Ntree. Uh I never heard a tree. I try to
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.24,1:05:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,be kind to trees. You see, some people\Nwill take an axe, a hand axe, and
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.55,1:06:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going by a tree. They slam it\Ninto the tree and then walk on, pull it
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.96,1:06:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,out and walk on. What do you think? The\Ntree didn't know you just hit it with an
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.20,1:06:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,axe.\NIf you ask the tree, "How was that?" The
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.76,1:06:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,tree will go, "Ow."\NAll of life then is aware of the nature
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.24,1:06:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of other of the other life. In an\Nadvanced state of consciousness, you'll
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.68,1:06:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,see\Nthat even a tree is aware of the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.72,1:06:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity of yourself. The self with a\Ncapital S.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.68,1:06:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,As you walk by a tree, its\Nconsciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.16,1:06:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which any scientist would poo,\Nis aware of the divinity of that which
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.03,1:06:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is walking by.\NThat's true. Is this true? Even a tree
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.68,1:07:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is aware of the divinity,\Nthe godness within you. The tree is
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.11,1:07:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,aware\Nthat a emissary of God is walking by.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.44,1:07:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try it again. Even a tree is aware\Nthat you are an emissary of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.44,1:07:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Even a tree is aware.\NAll of nature knows
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.59,1:07:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that that which is of divine origin is\Nwalking by.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.07,1:07:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All the more reason to be kind to it. If\Nconsciousness expressed his life is
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.48,1:07:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,aware of the divinity of your essence\Nand bows to it out of respect for that
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.03,1:07:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,life, you return the favor. And\Ntherefore, I love the trees. I love the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.92,1:07:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,kitties. I love the doggies. I love all\Nliving things.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.52,1:07:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because their essence is also that of\Ndivinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.68,1:07:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is God appearing as a kitty cat.\NThis is God appearing as a mole. This is
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.40,1:08:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,God appearing as a toad.\NYou see the little toad.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.35,1:08:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see? The toad loves life.\NHe loves
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.88,1:08:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,being a toad.\NSo to take a hammer and hit the toad
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.96,1:08:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,as you can see the extreme\Nungodliness of that
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.35,1:08:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it's divi because that is denying the\Ndivinity of all that exists. All that
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.12,1:08:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,exists is worthy of reverence.\NSo we as we grow we begin to revere all
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.60,1:08:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of life in all of its expressions.\NEven the mad dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.12,1:08:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the mad dog which can't help but be\Na mad dog. Even the raving maniac who
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.04,1:08:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,can't help but be a raving maniac\Ncan they cannot help themsself.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.79,1:09:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of benevolence then\Nuh you send unconditional love to all of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.92,1:09:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,life and wish it well.\NYou differentiate appearance from
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.31,1:09:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,essence. Be kind to all of life.\NAnd so you so you can practice with
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.71,1:09:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,this. It's very beneficial to have pets\Nand a garden spot. Now, the pet could be
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.00,1:09:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,anything. The pet could be cockroaches\Nin a little box. The pet could be
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.19,1:09:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,anything.\NMy mother used to make me let them go.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.96,1:09:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't keep them in the box. She said,\N"Those are cockroaches."
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.64,1:09:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. decrease your expectations of\Nothers.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.52,1:09:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's going to ever reach the uh the\Nlevel at which you would wish them.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.52,1:09:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nso the expectation has to be mllified
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.96,1:10:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can see that everybody has been\Nprogrammed by our society.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.08,1:10:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So few are the people who escape the\Nprogramming uh of our
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.40,1:10:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,uh human world.\NIt's m it's very good for your peace of
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.96,1:10:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,mind to mind your own business.\NMind your own business.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.64,1:10:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind your own business. Oh dear.\NMake a list of your worries. Oh dear. If
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.44,1:10:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't get rid of your worries, then\Nit's important to make a list of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.19,1:10:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everybody here got any worries?\NAnybody here? Anybody here who doesn't
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.04,1:10:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,who doesn't have any worries?\NAll right. The metal ward is that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.56,1:10:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,One way to get on top of your worries is\Nto make a list of them and prioritize
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.36,1:11:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,them because when you identify them, you\Ncan deal with deal with them. Otherwise,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.67,1:11:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they're just sort of a vague vague\Nthing. worrying about money, worrying
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.76,1:11:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about old age, worrying about\Nuh your business collapsing, whatever it
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.32,1:11:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is. Uh if you sit down and make a list\Nof worries, they lose a good deal of
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.48,1:11:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,power over you because you're defining\Nthem. When you define them, you confine
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.23,1:11:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,them and you see how small they actually\Nare.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.44,1:11:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, if you go flat broke, you go in\Nthe county.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.32,1:11:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's wrong with being on the\Ncounty? Sure. If you're flat broke, got
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.15,1:11:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,no money, no place to go,\Nwhat better place to be?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.88,1:11:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Chocolate versus vanilla is simply a\Nchoice.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.12,1:11:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. that what the world does it\Nit says uh the people on this side are
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.96,1:11:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,chocolate and the people on this side\Nare vanilla
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.64,1:12:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nthey don't have to be seen as
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.67,1:12:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,adversaries.\NYou can see you can really choose you
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.60,1:12:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,can choose chocolate doesn't mean you\Nhave to hate vanilla.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.32,1:12:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can choose vanilla doesn't mean you\Nyou have to hate chocolate. If you watch
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.44,1:12:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the political news, you would think the\Nonly way you can be vanilla is you got
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.04,1:12:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to hate chocolate or vice versa.\NActually, you're just picking one of two
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.32,1:12:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,choices.\NDifferentiate your emotional from your
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.40,1:12:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual viewpoints.\NPeople will use an excuse, well, I feel
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.71,1:12:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this way.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.40,1:12:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,they use the emotional outlet.\NWhy did you do that? Well, I felt I felt
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.67,1:12:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,like that. That's the big excuse. That\Nwas my your emotional viewpoint. And
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.15,1:12:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what was your spiritual viewpoint? Well,\Nmy spiritual viewpoint is somewhat
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.12,1:13:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,different. So, you don't want to be the\Nslave of the ego and its emotions. And
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.64,1:13:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,don't forget that the ego the basis of\Nthe mind is the child. So when you're
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.08,1:13:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about emo emotions very often\Nyou're to talking about the inner child
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.36,1:13:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and not the inner adult\Nand in fighting your way out of some
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.60,1:13:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,corner emotional corner use logic\Ninstead of emotion. A lot of people try
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.84,1:13:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,emotion instead of just logic. If you\Nuse logic you can see there's nothing to
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.92,1:13:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,be afraid of. When life is over they\Nbury you and that's the end of the
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.08,1:13:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,problem. So what's the problem?\NWhen it's over, it's over. No more
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.64,1:13:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering.\NAsk for a miracle. Those of you who have
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.40,1:13:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,done the course of miracles know that\Nthis in itself is a miracle. That off
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.08,1:14:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,asking for a miracle\Nvery often produces the miracle. I
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.23,1:14:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot find a thing. I have no idea\Nwhere it is. is a complete blank and
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.88,1:14:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask the Holy Spirit. I'll say,\N"Where is so and so?" And then I forget
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.08,1:14:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it. I walk in the other room and then\Nout of nowhere, not out of logic, out of
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.15,1:14:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,nowhere, it comes to my mind, you left\Nit in the bathroom on the shelf. Got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.60,1:14:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything I ever lose is in the\Nbathroom in the c in the shelf or the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.60,1:14:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,kitchen on the shelf.\NHuh? Ask for a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.67,1:14:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,People feel they're not entitled to\Nmiracles or that they don't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.52,1:14:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, people don't know what a miracle\Nis. Very often, a miracle is merely the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.40,1:14:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,refraraming. The thing has been\Nreframed, especially in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.36,1:15:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't expected in time. Today is\Ntomorrow's yesterday. Today
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.08,1:15:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is tomorrow is yesterday. Good God, it's\Nyesterday already. And here I'm worrying
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.56,1:15:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,about it.\NI was worrying about getting back here
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.12,1:15:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,on time\Nand tomorrow that's going to be
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.48,1:15:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,yesterday. Today's going to be yesterday\Nand we'll say we were worried about
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.60,1:15:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,getting back on time. Yeah, yesterday\Naside from having a mentor, talking
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.32,1:15:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,things over with friends is really very\Nimportant. Very important. The isolated
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.92,1:15:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,person ends up pretty crazy\Nand u
