Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.56,1:15:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,uh sh and he terrified all of industry\Nand all he didn't have any friends to
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.32,1:15:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,talk it over with.\NI forget his name now.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.76,1:16:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Huh?\NThe uni bomber. That's it. The uni
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.28,1:16:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,bomber had nobody to talk it over with.\NIf he talked it over with, friends, he
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.44,1:16:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,might have been dissuaded.\NHe might have been dissuaded. No, he
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.88,1:16:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to be all by himself\Nin an 8 by10
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.32,1:16:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,space.\NI understand he is now all by himself in
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.88,1:16:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a 10 by12 space.\NHe probably feels he's rattling around
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.08,1:16:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in that big cell.\NAs you can see, the person with
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.12,1:16:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,schizophrenia\Nand delusions
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.56,1:16:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is unable to help themsself.\NSo even though he was the uni bomber,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.64,1:16:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't hate him. You can't want to\Nget even with him. How can you see the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.52,1:17:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,uni bomber\Nexcept as a person who was spiritually
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.08,1:17:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,lost?\NHe was spiritually lost. Spiritually
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.32,1:17:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,lost. Spiritually lost to completely\Negocentric.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.64,1:17:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So not having friends to talk it\Nover with.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.44,1:17:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Another way to down your fears and\Nworries is accept the worst possible
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.92,1:17:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,scenario.\NWorst possible scenario. Picture it in
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.12,1:17:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,your mind. Well, the worst thing that\Ncan happen is I get a flat tire on the
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.96,1:17:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Parkway and it's raining\Nand uh I forgot my driver's license.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.44,1:17:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the worst possible scenario.\NThen you say, "Well, now what if all
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.15,1:17:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that happened?"\NWell, I'd catch hell from the cop and
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.15,1:17:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have to pay the fine. That's true.\NWell, if that's the worst possible
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.71,1:17:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,scenario, you don't have to be\Nfrightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.76,1:18:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,One time,\None time I left Phoenix
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.19,1:18:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to to go up to uh where is it we live?\NUm, wherever it is we live and
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.92,1:18:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it's two hours away, two, a couple hours\Nnorth of Phoenix. And I started to leave
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.71,1:18:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Phoenix and my headlights went out. The\Nbattery went dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.44,1:18:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here I am 110 or whatever it is\Nmiles and it's midnight, pitch blackout,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.00,1:18:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've got no headlights.\NWell, wouldn't do me much good to pull
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.48,1:18:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,over the side of the road. So, what I\Ndid is I followed the car ahead of me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.80,1:18:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I very carefully did everything he\Ndid. When he went this way, I went that
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.15,1:18:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,way.\NI knew that sooner or later the driver
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.84,1:18:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to see some guy with his lights\Nout is behind me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.32,1:18:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and he would conclude that this guy's\Nfollowing me home because he's got no
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.92,1:18:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,lights.\NSo I followed him for two hours,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.15,1:19:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,150 miles or whatever the distance is.\NAnd I I was worried that I was
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.44,1:19:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,frightening the guy. So I asked God, I\Nsaid, "Please don't let him be
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.80,1:19:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,frightened. I just need him to guide me\Nhome." And the guy, I think he did
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.56,1:19:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,understand it. He eventually did\Nunderstand it. And he got that I was a
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.04,1:19:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,man in distress and uh let's let's I\Nhave permission to ask this. He he
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.80,1:19:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,finally got it. Resist. Yeah, he got it.\NI was praying that he would get it. I
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.36,1:19:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,said, "Dear God, please let him just get\Nthat. I got to get up the highway and I
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.67,1:19:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,got no headlights."\NSo that worked out. That was the worst
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.80,1:19:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,possible scenario.\NI like this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.64,1:19:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the movie that should have won\Nthe best film ever.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.36,1:19:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Scarlet a hero. They named some other\Nmovie. Uh I couldn't understand why they
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.76,1:19:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,picked the movie they did when obviously\Nthis is the greatest movie ever made.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.71,1:20:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. And Scarlet would say, "I'll think\Nabout it tomorrow."
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.48,1:20:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in the modern world, that would be\Ncriticized, wouldn't it? Think about it
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.15,1:20:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,tomorrow. You're this, that, and the\Nother. But there's a certain wisdom to
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.80,1:20:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that because if you think about it\Ntomorrow, it doesn't look the same. For
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.19,1:20:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,one thing, you've started a process\Ngoing in your unconscious mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.40,1:20:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And so when you say, "I can't think of\Nhow I'm going to make any money. I
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.52,1:20:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't got any assets and I got no\Nincome and I've been cut off now." And
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.08,1:20:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you say, "Well, I'll think about it\Ntomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.56,1:20:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll think about it tomorrow."\NThen suddenly in the morning you get up
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.84,1:20:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're you self boiling an egg and\Nall of a sudden you remind yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.60,1:20:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,well I could take this to a hawk shop\Nand probably get a couple hundred bucks,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.96,1:20:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,right? Yesterday you didn't think of\Nthat. Today it's obvious everybody's got
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.23,1:20:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,some something in your house you can\Nhawk.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.60,1:21:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody got something you can hawk\Nhawkables.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.44,1:21:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody so poor they haven't even got a\Nhawkable?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.32,1:21:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's that poor. You can you may have\Nto sleep on the floor, but you but you
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.23,1:21:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,got something to hawk.\NThere's a new program on that called H.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.04,1:21:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it? Hawk Shop or something about\Nthe same night as Ice Road Triggers.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.71,1:21:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Pawn shop. Yeah.\NIs peace. Peace uh is everywhere
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.76,1:21:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,existent.\NPeace is existent all the time. Even in
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.76,1:21:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the midst of war. Even in the midst of\Nwar, you know, we're about to explode.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.80,1:21:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This mind was about to go off. And he\Nsays, "Well, we might get killed." And
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.52,1:21:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then, you know, he said, "Then what\Nhappens if we go off?" And I said to
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.44,1:21:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,him, "Well, then we die." He said,\N"You're right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.00,1:22:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right." And his fear went away.\Nand uh just the peace in the middle of
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.44,1:22:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,war.\NThere was peace in that you were doing
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.12,1:22:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly what your duty was. You were\Nsupposed to man this particular gun. You
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.15,1:22:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,were supposed to watch for strange\Nships. You were supposed to be on guard,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.40,1:22:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,report anything.\NUh and so you're standing out there. We
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.36,1:22:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,were I was on a very small ship, not one\Nof these big battleships where I was out
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.60,1:22:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,on a mind sweeper. And so uh we stood\Nwatch for four hours at night, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.28,1:22:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you stood watch, you wear the\Ngun belt with a for loaded 45.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.15,1:22:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Loaded 45. And anything that moved, you\Nshot it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.00,1:22:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,See something moving over the fan tail.\NUh anyway, things could be worse.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.71,1:22:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is transitory.\NSo that's another thing. The ego thinks
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.80,1:22:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's eternal, that its life is\Ngoing to be forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.28,1:23:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you accept the fact that life\Nis transitory at best,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.15,1:23:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we're all going to go. Uh-oh. You didn't\Nexpect to hear that today.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.23,1:23:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all going to go.\NAnybody thinks they're not going to go?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.92,1:23:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody planning not to go?\NIn the infinite dimensions of time,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.48,1:23:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we're all living together.\NYou would think a couple years here and
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.88,1:23:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,there is different in time. But in\Ncompared to infinite time, in the few
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.08,1:23:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,decades or whatever it is it'll take for\Nall of us to go over on the other side,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.28,1:23:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it's all about the same time. So\Nfrankly, we're all going over about the
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.15,1:23:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,same time.\NSome people went ahead and got parking
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.00,1:23:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,places for us.\NOne of my best friends is over and found
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.52,1:24:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,us parking places. So we get to heaven,\Nwe will have parking places and uh a
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.40,1:24:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,sign telling us where to go. See,\Nlife is transitory.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.92,1:24:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The acceptance of that then decreases a\Ngreat deal of fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.19,1:24:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Life and all experience of life is\Ntransitory.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.44,1:24:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The knowledge that you were created by\NGod, it then gives a certain semnity,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.23,1:24:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,certain profoundity. Let's see if we\Nhave permission to ask that. We have
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.63,1:24:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,permission to ask this question.\NWe were all created by God. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.52,1:24:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We were created by God. Wow. here. You\Nthought it was a sperm and an egg,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.08,1:25:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a biologic accident.\NLife is transitory.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.88,1:25:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you really are was created by\NGod.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.36,1:25:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, not the ego, but the self with a\Ncapital L S is the essence of who you
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.67,1:25:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,are. And when you leave the body, those\Nof you who have left the experience of
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.92,1:25:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,leaving the body, the witness observer\Nwitnesses and observes the body but
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.56,1:25:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,feels no attraction to it at all. It\Nseems uh meaningless, boring,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.52,1:25:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,not even attractive. You would think\Nyou're trying to get back in that body
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.88,1:25:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and reactivate it, but strangely enough,\Nit just lays there and it has no
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.63,1:25:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,attraction.\NYou go on a worry diet. We said we were
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.44,1:25:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,going to make a list of worries. So then\Nyou begin to pick off your worry diet.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.71,1:25:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The things that you're going to let be\Nwilling to let go of. I will stop
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.19,1:25:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,worrying about money.\NWorst can happen to you if you don't
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.28,1:26:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,have any money is you're poor.\NWell, I've been poor. When you're poor,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.92,1:26:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,there's lots of things you can't have.\NCan't have a new Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.04,1:26:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you go on a diet and you let start\Nletting things go. Could I be happy
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.40,1:26:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,without a new Cadillac? Yep.\NCould I be happy if I didn't have a new
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.40,1:26:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,pair of shoes? Yep. I got them on, so I\Nknow.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.00,1:26:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up on a worry diet. Give up trying\Nto be happy. Just
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.40,1:26:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you have an ongoing acceptance. Now this\Nacceptance is not the human will.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.36,1:26:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This acceptance is being the witness\Nobserver. It's a contemplative position.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.32,1:26:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Not meditative but contemplative.\NSo that as we walk through the day today
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.52,1:27:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the stage is here where it is. The\Nflowers are where they are. Susan is
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.63,1:27:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting there doing fine. There's some\Nmysterious person in the dark over
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.23,1:27:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,there.\NI don't have to know who that mysterious
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.32,1:27:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,person is.\NI said, I can control my curiosity. Do I
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.28,1:27:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,have to know who's sitting there in the\Ndark? No. Don't have to. Do I know who's
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.63,1:27:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting there?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.36,1:27:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I presume it's a friend.\NWell, if it's not a friend, it could be
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.67,1:27:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,an enemy.\NIf it's an not If it's an enemy, it
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.40,1:27:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,could kill you right now.\NSo, here I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.40,1:28:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to kill me? Kill me.\NNobody killed me.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.36,1:28:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh well.\NYou were created by God. You can let go
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.32,1:28:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,your worries one by one by total\Nacceptance.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.32,1:28:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up trying to be happy. Don't try to\Nbe happy. Just be happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.44,1:28:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try to be happy. Just be happy.\NThat's simpler than trying to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.80,1:28:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see that trying to be happy is\Nlike a mouse chasing its tail.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.67,1:28:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop trying to be happy and just be\Nhappy.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.63,1:28:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should you be happy? You should be\Nhappy because you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.36,1:28:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You are fantastic.\NFrom nothingness to somethingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.92,1:29:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up trying to be happy.\NGive up being rich and famous. Oh,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.96,1:29:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody's dream in America. I can't go\Nto Hollywood and get on the television
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.36,1:29:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,interview shows.\NGive up being rich and famous.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.52,1:29:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what happens to most rich and\Nfamous people.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.23,1:29:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's rather grizzly when you study the\Ntruth of their life, their life stories.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.96,1:29:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up being rich and famous. what\Npeople do to be rich and famous. Have 18
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.71,1:29:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,children at once. God knows what people\Nwill do. Uh walk the tight rope over uh
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.67,1:29:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,stretches. Who was that great uh\Ngymnast that finally fell to his death?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.15,1:29:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Famous circus family.\NAnyway, Italian name. He was the
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.63,1:29:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,greatest in the world and he fell to his\Ndeath anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.60,1:30:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So being rich and famous\Neggs you on to the edge. People with any
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.60,1:30:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,sense, you know, stand back a little.\NYou see, every year about nine people
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.23,1:30:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,fall over the edge of the Grand Canyon.\NHow did they manage that?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.48,1:30:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was scared to get within 20 ft of the\Nedge of the Grand Canyon.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.04,1:30:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I've gotten better. I used to be 50 feet\Nfrom the edge of the Grand Canyon. Now
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.28,1:30:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I've gotten I'm up to 20 feet within the\NGrand Canyon.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.08,1:30:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How do they get over there where they\Nfall off?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.12,1:30:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Every year about nine people falls into\Nthe Grand Canyon.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.56,1:30:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who's dumb enough to fall in the\NGrand Canyon deserves falling in the
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.23,1:30:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Canyon.\NI think they actually they're just
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.56,1:30:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,daredevils. You know these people that\Nwant to parachute out of strange things
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.19,1:31:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,at strange heights with both legs bound\Ntogether and a gag in their mouth or
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.23,1:31:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,something.\NIt's what I call vain glorious. What a
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.28,1:31:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of people think it's heroics is\Nnothing but vain glory. They want to be
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.44,1:31:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,on the headlines. They jumped all the\Nway from,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.12,1:31:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, 30,000 ft and didn't open\Ntheir parachute until they got to 600
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.63,1:31:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,feet down here. So, they must have had\Nan exciting ride.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.92,1:31:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Nmore spiritual ways are to walk the
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.52,1:31:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,labyrinth and you know you the walking\Nthe labyrinth. What cathedral was that?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.08,1:31:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, what cathedral was that? The\Nlabyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.80,1:31:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Shark. Shark.\N>> Shark.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.40,1:31:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, walking the labyrinth, which is\Nvery famous. Our church back home has a
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.88,1:31:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,copy of the labyrinth in the parking\Nlot.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.71,1:31:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The effect of walking the labyrinth is\Nthe same.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.40,1:32:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you trace it with a pencil, if you\Nhave an a diagram of the labyrinth and
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.67,1:32:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you take a pencil point, you start from\Nthe starting point and you do with the
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.84,1:32:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,pencil point. You follow the labyrinth\Nwhere it goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.63,1:32:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The effect on your consciousness is the\Nsame as if you walked it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.44,1:32:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that strange?\NOkay, that's mystical.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.32,1:32:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh that is a mystical truth.\NNobody knows the reason for it. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.56,1:32:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody knows the reason for it.\NIt's just the fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.88,1:32:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can if you're really worried and\Ncannot get off of it, you find some
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.48,1:32:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,place that has the labyrinth in the\Nparking lot or something or you get a
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.96,1:32:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,copy of the labyrinth and you trace it\Nslowly
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.36,1:32:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with the tip of a pencil\Nand you follow it says go this way. Go
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.12,1:33:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this way now go this way now go this\Nway. There's something about the this
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.48,1:33:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,mysterious pattern\Nthat brings a profound sense of peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.96,1:33:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Profound sense of peace from merely\Nfollowing a diagram with your eye or
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.28,1:33:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,your pencil or if it's large walking it.\NWalk the labyrinth.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.19,1:33:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Something similar is to do the rosary.\NDo the rosary.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.71,1:33:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Something similar is spinning the prayer\Nwheel.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.40,1:33:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. All right. Let's ask if those all\Nwork. Doing the ro rosary brings about
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.80,1:33:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,greater inner peace.\NSpinning the prayer wheel brings about
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.19,1:33:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,greater inner peace. Resist. So whether\Nyou're Christian, Buddhist, or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.56,1:33:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't say you have to be a\NChristian or a believer to do these
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.84,1:33:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,things. Just says do them. doesn't say\Nonly Christians benefit from the
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.84,1:34:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,labyrinth or only Buddhists benefit from\Nthe prayer wheel. Says anybody anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.28,1:34:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's something beyond beliefs\Nbeyond belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.32,1:34:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some other power and energy and\Npatterning in the universe
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.28,1:34:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,uh which nobody has discovered as yet.\NIn my perusal of the world's spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.08,1:34:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,literature over decades, I've never come\Nacross any explanation why such a
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.67,1:34:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,geometric pattern should have such a\Nprofound profound effect. There is some
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.67,1:34:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,recent research on the Taurus and this\NTaurus T Ru shape and
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.63,1:34:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,uh in the mathematics thereof could be\Nperhaps a plausible explanation
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.96,1:34:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,uh partial explanation. Okay. Do the\Nrosary, walk the labyrinth, and spin the
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.48,1:34:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,prayer wheel. Another thing that will\Ncalm your nerves is to write your will
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.08,1:35:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and take out life insurance.\NAnybody here lacks life insurance?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.28,1:35:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Oh. Oh. Oh.\NAnybody here hasn't written a will?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.36,1:35:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Oh. Oh. Oh. Oh. Oh. Oh.\NThe fact that you're mortal
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.23,1:35:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,uh and the acceptance of your mortality.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.67,1:35:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to not have a will, etc. No life\Ninsurance uh means you a loss of sense
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.44,1:35:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of reality.\NIn reality, you're going to come to an
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.84,1:35:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,end.\NCan't tell you that. But
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.80,1:35:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is this news to anybody? Few arms go up.\NYep. It does come to an end. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.88,1:35:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody you might as well benefit.\NYou're going to croak anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.80,1:36:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You watch on TV, you can get life\Ninsurance pretty darn cheap nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.32,1:36:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Kick out a friend or relative. Leave it\Nto the Humane Society.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.08,1:36:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't have any friends or\Nrelatives, what about all the little
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.08,1:36:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,doggies and kitties that have no home?\NYou can make a will and leave a life
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.60,1:36:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,insurance policy to the humane society.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.67,1:36:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the importance of those things?\NBecause there's a certain generosity
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.52,1:36:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh a lovingness that your death will\Nserve some positive benefit to life in
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.28,1:36:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,its various forms.\NThe mean society could use the insurance
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.84,1:36:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,money so it can find more homes for more\Nhomeless pets etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.88,1:36:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Bread a will. Take out life insurance.\NWatch television's Animal Channel.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.71,1:36:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Animal Channel has very interesting\Nthings on it. Yep. And bury the hatchet.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.48,1:37:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Bury the hatchet.\NI went to a camp and when the boys would
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.11,1:37:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,get into scramble each other at\Nmidnight, they would get off to get up.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.23,1:37:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to go out and dig a hole and you\Nhad to put your hatchet in there and
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.80,1:37:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then bury it.\NThat was a nuisance. who wants to get up
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.60,1:37:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at midnight and go dig a hole in the\Ndark. We were all scared of the dark
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.76,1:37:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway cuz we were all about 12 or\Nsomething.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.08,1:37:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we learned how to avoid needing to\Nbury the hatchet.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.44,1:37:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up being an adrenaline junkie.\NThat's a hard one. You see all these
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.00,1:37:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,speeders, you know, they're caught going\N110 on the Parkway. They're always in
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.48,1:37:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Los Angeles and they're always going 100\Nand you see the helicopter following
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.15,1:37:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,them hour after hour after hour.\NFinally, he gets so bored of watching
